What you need to know:  President William Ruto and his deputy Rigathi Gachagua have urged farmers who are still keeping maize to release it before the arrival of 4 million bags of duty-free maize into the countryNation. Africa established that most farmers in the North Rift,  have already sold their maizeMost small scale farmers in the region sold the produce in January after the government announced plans to import duty-free maize last month